name: Venusaur ex

abilities.name: Tranquil Flower
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may heal 60 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

attack.name: Dangerous Toxwhip
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Ledyba
flavorText: When the weather turns cold, lots of Ledyba gather from everywhere to cluster and keep each other warm.

name: Ledian

abilities.name: Glittering Star Pattern
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon that has 90 HP or less remaining to the Active Spot.

flavorText: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.

attack.name: Swift
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance, or by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Celebi
flavorText: This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.

attack.name: Collect
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Lileep
flavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

attack.name: Bind Down
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Cradily

abilities.name: Selective Slime
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose Burned, Confused, or Poisoned. Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition.

flavorText: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast, but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

attack.name: Miasma Wind
attack.text: This attack does 100 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Carnivine
flavorText: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

attack.name: Nosh
attack.text: Heal 40 damage from this Pokémon.

attack.name: Loom Over
attack.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Mow Rotom
flavorText: This Rotom has possessed a lawn mower. It will mow down grass and flowers, then swagger around with pride at its accomplishments.

attack.name: Reaping Dash
attack.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools and Special Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Grubbin
flavorText: It spits sticky threads and winds them around branches, then swings nimbly from tree to tree in a pendulum-like motion.

attack.name: Ambush
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Gossifleur
flavorText: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg, then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight, its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

attack.name: Double Spin
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Eldegoss
flavorText: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokémon can benefit from them.

attack.name: Breezy Gift
attack.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your deck. If you do, search your deck for up to 3 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Applin
flavorText: Applin lives inside an apple. When an Applin is separated from its apple, its body loses moisture and the Pokémon grows weak.

name: Dipplin
flavorText: The head sticking out belongs to the fore-wyrm, while the tail belongs to the core-wyrm. The two share one apple and help each other out.

attack.name: Coated Attack
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Basic Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Hydrapple ex

abilities.name: Ripening Charge
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic {G} Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, heal 30 damage from that Pokémon.

attack.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, heal 30 damage from that Pokémon.

attack.name: Syrup Storm
attack.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Grass Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Nymble
flavorText: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

name: Lokix
flavorText: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

name: Toedscool
flavorText: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

name: Toedscruel
flavorText: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

attack.name: Mega Drain
attack.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

attack.name: Burning Run
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Pansear
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

attack.name: Call for Family
attack.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Searing Flame
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Reshiram
flavorText: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

name: Salandit
flavorText: Only female Salandit can produce gas laden with pheromones. Males entranced by this gas will do whatever the females tell them.

attack.name: Ember
attack.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Salazzle
flavorText: When two Salazzle meet, they will use their pheromone gas to fight over the males in each other’s group.

attack.name: Sudden Scorching
attack.text: Your opponent discards a card from their hand. If this Pokémon evolved from Salandit during this turn, your opponent discards 2 more cards.

attack.name: Flamethrower
attack.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Turtonator
flavorText: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

attack.name: Ring of Fire
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Burned. During your opponent’s next turn, that Pokémon can’t retreat.

attack.name: Inferno Onrush
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 60 damage to itself.

name: Scorbunny
flavorText: Fire energy gathers in the pads of its feet, raising their temperature. Once hot, Scorbunny’s footpads can deal heavy damage to opponents.

attack.name: Quick Attack
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Raboot
flavorText: While it prides itself on its varied kicking moves, it can also deliver powerful headbutts once its flames have heated up its forehead.

name: Cinderace ex

attack.name: Flare Strike
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use Flare Strike.

attack.name: Garnet Volley
attack.text: This attack does 180 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Charcadet
flavorText: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Blastoise ex

abilities.name: Solid Shell
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Twin Cannons
attack.text: Discard up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 140 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Lapras
flavorText: It loves crossing the sea with people and Pokémon on its back. It understands human speech.

name: Lapras ex

attack.name: Power Splash
attack.text: This attack does 40 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attack.name: Larimar Rain
attack.text: Look at the top 20 cards of your deck and attach any number of Energy cards you find there to your Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Marill
flavorText: The oil-filled end of its tail floats on water. It keeps Marill from drowning even in a strong current.

name: Azumarill
flavorText: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of living things on riverbeds.

attack.name: Bubble Beam
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Finneon
flavorText: It absorbs sunlight with the pink areas of its skin, which then shine. This appears to be a form of camouflage.

name: Lumineon
flavorText: Lumineon swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.

attack.name: Return
attack.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

name: Tirtouga
flavorText: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

attack.name: Splashing Turn
attack.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Carracosta

abilities.name: Primal Knowledge
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent’s Active Evolution Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta’s own shell grows thick and sturdy.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: Frogadier
flavorText: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja ex

attack.name: Shifting Shuriken
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Crabominable

abilities.name: Food Prep
abilities.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon cost {C} less for each Kofu card in your discard pile.

flavorText: Though its punches are powerful, this Pokémon’s movements are sluggish. It blows icy bubbles from its mouth to immobilize its opponents.

attack.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon cost Colorless less for each Kofu card in your discard pile.

attack.name: Haymaker
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use Haymaker.

name: Chewtle
flavorText: A popular game among children is to lift up sticks that Chewtle have bitten onto to see whose Chewtle can hang on the longest.

name: Drednaw

abilities.name: Impervious Shell
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon if that damage is 200 or more.

flavorText: Drednaw lurks along the shoreline. When prey come to drink water, Drednaw stretches its neck out and chomps down on them.

attack.name: Hard Crunch
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Veluza

abilities.name: Food Prep
abilities.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon cost {C} less for each Kofu card in your discard pile.

flavorText: Veluza has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.

attack.text: Attacks used by this Pokémon cost Colorless less for each Kofu card in your discard pile.

attack.name: Sonic Edge
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

attack.name: Collect
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Electivire
flavorText: This Pokémon presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent and instantly sends over 20,000 volts of high-voltage electricity through them.

attack.name: Unleash Lightning
attack.text: During your next turn, your Pokémon can’t attack. (This includes new Pokémon that come into play.)

name: Chinchou
flavorText: It shoots positively and negatively charged electricity from the tips of its two antennae and stuns its opponents.

attack.name: Double Voltage
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Lanturn
flavorText: It blinds prey with an intense burst of light. With the prey incapacitated, the Pokémon swallows it in a single gulp.

attack.name: Disorienting Flash
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused. Put 8 damage counters instead of 3 on that Pokémon for this Special Condition.

attack.name: Thunderous Bolt
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Since it can’t generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

attack.name: Jolting Charge
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Grass Energy cards and up to 2 Basic Lightning Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Galvantula ex

attack.name: Charged Web
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex or Pokémon V, this attack does 110 more damage.

attack.name: Fulgurite
attack.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon. During your opponent’s next turn, they can’t play any Item cards from their hand.

name: Charjabug
flavorText: As it digests fallen leaves, it generates and stores electricity, which it can discharge from the tips of its jaws.

attack.name: Parallel Placement
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Charjabug and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Vikavolt
flavorText: When carrying a Charjabug, Vikavolt can receive electricity from it and then rapidly fire powerful electromagnetic beams from its large jaws.

attack.name: Volt Switch
attack.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Lightning Pokémon.

name: Togedemaru
flavorText: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

attack.name: Electrifying Chance
attack.text: If you have exactly 1 Prize card remaining, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.

attack.name: Combat Thunder
attack.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon.

name: Pawmi
flavorText: The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. Pawmi fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.

attack.name: Targeted Spark
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Slowpoke
flavorText: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

attack.name: Dangle Tail
attack.text: Put a Pokémon from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Slowking
flavorText: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation, it remains calm and collected.

attack.name: Seek Inspiration
attack.text: Discard the top card of your deck, and if that card is a Pokémon that doesn’t have a Rule Box, choose 1 of its attacks and use it as this attack. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: Because of the way it floats aimlessly, an old folktale calls it a “signpost for wandering spirits.”

attack.name: Expand
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Drifblim
flavorText: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.

attack.name: Everyone Explode Now
attack.text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Drifloon and Drifblim in play. This attack also does 30 damage to each of your Drifloon and Drifblim. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Yamask
flavorText: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

attack.name: Ominous Eyes
attack.text: Put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon.

name: Comfey
flavorText: It prefers areas with lots of flowers. A Comfey adorned with flowers is a happy Comfey, and the flowers gain healing effects.

attack.name: Flower Shower
attack.text: Each player draws 3 cards.

attack.name: Play Rough
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Milcery
flavorText: When attacked, it tackles its foe and covers them in cream. With its foe either blinded or astonished by deliciousness, Milcery flees.

name: Alcremie
flavorText: Alcremie that have been cherished produce exquisite cream, so Trainers always raise them lovingly.

attack.name: Colorful Confection
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 5 Pokémon that are the same type as any Basic Energy attached to this Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Fidough
flavorText: The yeast in Fidough’s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokémon has been protected by people since long ago.

attack.name: Pleasant Aroma
attack.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dachsbun ex

abilities.name: Time to Chow Down
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may heal all damage from each of your Evolution Pokémon. If you healed any damage in this way, discard all Energy from those Pokémon.

attack.name: Wonder Shine
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Flittle
flavorText: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon’s belly.

name: Espathra
flavorText: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.

name: Greavard
flavorText: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.

name: Iron Boulder
flavorText: It was named after a mysterious object recorded in an old book. Its body seems to be metallic.

attack.name: Adjusted Horn
attack.text: If you don’t have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does nothing.

name: Cubone
flavorText: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears, its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

attack.name: Reckless Charge
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Marowak
flavorText: This Pokémon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely, using a bone as a weapon.

attack.name: Growl
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do 40 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Bone Vengeance
attack.text: If any of your Benched Cubone have any damage counters on them, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Rhyhorn
flavorText: Once it starts running, it won’t stop—even if it crashes through boulders. This disposition is what’s caused its habitat to expand.

name: Rhydon
flavorText: It evolved to walk using only its hind legs, which has allowed it to expand its habitat even onto steep mountains.

attack.name: Destructive Horn
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Rhyperior

abilities.name: Wide Wall
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever your opponent plays a Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to all of your Pokémon.

flavorText: A Rhyperior’s brain is smaller than a Rhydon’s, but the Rhyperior is stronger because it spends more energy on battling and less on brainpower.

attack.name: Drill Run
attack.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

attack.name: Calm Mind
attack.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Medicham
flavorText: It elegantly avoids attacks with dance-like steps, then launches a devastating blow in the same motion.

attack.name: Double Smash
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Medicham ex

attack.name: Chi-Atsu
attack.text: Put damage counters on your opponent’s Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 50.

attack.name: Yoga Kick
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It has the peculiar power of being able to see emotions, such as joy and rage, in the form of waves.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Lucario ex
Mienfoo
flavorText: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

attack.name: Knock Off
attack.text: Discard a random card from your opponent’s hand.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

attack.name: Gale Roundhouse
attack.text: If your opponent has 5 or fewer cards in their hand, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Pancham
flavorText: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master’s actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

attack.name: Leer
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Diancie
flavorText: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

attack.name: Diffuse Reflection
attack.text: This attack does 40 damage for each Special Energy attached to all of your opponent’s Pokémon.

name: Crabrawler
flavorText: If it loses its pincers, they’ll quickly regrow. The pincers are popular ingredients in paella since their shells produce a tasty soup stock.

name: Falinks
flavorText: The leader, known as the brass, uses its extendible horn to issue orders to the others when it’s time to change formation.

attack.name: Form Ranks
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: All-Out Attack
attack.text: If this Pokémon used Form Ranks during your last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Garganacl ex

abilities.name: Salty Body
abilities.text: This Pokémon can’t be affected by any Special Conditions.

attack.name: Block Hammer
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 60 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Koraidon
flavorText: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

attack.name: Resolute Fang
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Gulpin
flavorText: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.

attack.name: Super Poison Breath
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Swalot
flavorText: It can swallow a tire whole in one gulp. It secretes a horribly toxic fluid from the pores on its body.

attack.name: Devouring Mouth
attack.text: If this Pokémon has more Energy attached than your opponent’s Active Pokémon, this attack does 160 more damage.

attack.name: Venomous Hit
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Pangoro
flavorText: This Pokémon is quick to anger, and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.

attack.name: Pull
attack.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

attack.name: Tantrum
attack.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Impidimp
flavorText: They live in groups, pestering and playing pranks on each other to polish their troublemaking skills.

name: Morgrem
flavorText: This Pokémon absorbs negative emotions and turns them into energy. It’s popular with people who tend to think gloomy thoughts.

name: Grimmsnarl
flavorText: It lives deep within the forest. Even after evolving into this splendid form, it hasn’t given up on its petty misdeeds and pranks.

attack.name: Goad ‘n’ Grab
attack.text: Switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.) If you do, this attack does 160 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Knuckle Sandwich
attack.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Bombirdier
flavorText: Bombirdier uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.

attack.name: Reckless Charge
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Jirachi
flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

attack.name: Swelling Wish
attack.text: Attach a Basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

attack.name: Allure
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Klang
flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

attack.name: Iron Tackle
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

name: Klinklang

abilities.name: Emergency Rotation
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in your hand and your opponent has any Stage 2 Pokémon in play, you may put this Pokémon onto your Bench.

flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

attack.name: Hyper Ray
attack.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

name: Meltan
flavorText: It dissolves and eats metal. Circulating liquid metal within its body is how it generates energy.

attack.name: Knickknack Carrying
attack.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon Tool card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Melmetal
flavorText: At the end of its life-span, Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

attack.name: Reforged Axe
attack.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from this Pokémon. If you can’t discard any, this attack does nothing.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Melmetal ex

attack.name: Iron Swing
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Duraludon
flavorText: Its metal body is durable but prone to retaining heat. It vents this heat from the slits in its tail.

attack.name: Raging Hammer
attack.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Archaludon

abilities.name: Metal Bridge
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon that have {M} Energy attached have no Retreat Cost.

flavorText: It digs holes on mountains, searching for food. It’s so durable that being caught in a cave-in won’t faze it.

attack.text: All of your Pokémon that have Metal Energy attached have no Retreat Cost.

attack.name: Iron Blaster
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

name: Varoom
flavorText: The steel section is Varoom’s actual body. This Pokémon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.

name: Revavroom
flavorText: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.

name: Orthworm ex

abilities.name: Pummeling Payback
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon for each {M} Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attack.text: If this Pokémon is damaged by an attack from your opponent’s Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon for each Metal Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attack.name: Rock Tomb
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Raging Bolt
flavorText: It’s said to incinerate everything around it with lightning launched from its fur. Very little is known about this creature.

attack.name: Thunderburst Storm
attack.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Tauros
flavorText: A rowdy Pokémon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won’t stop until it hits something.

attack.name: Destructive Horn
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Eevee
flavorText: It can evolve into a variety of forms. Eevee’s genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.

attack.name: Call for Family
attack.text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: Since it tells time precisely, some countries consider it to be a deity of wisdom, versed in the ways of the world.

attack.name: Triple Stab
attack.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Noctowl

abilities.name: Jewel Seeker
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, if you have any Tera Pokémon in play, you may search your deck for up to 2 Trainer cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Its extremely soft wings make no sound in flight. It silently sneaks up on prey without being detected.

name: Glameow
flavorText: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: Purugly
flavorText: It would claim another Pokémon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

attack.name: Nyan Roll
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

name: Fan Rotom

abilities.name: Fan Call
abilities.text: Once during your first turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 {C} Pokémon with 100 HP or less, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can’t use more than 1 Fan Call Ability during your turn.

flavorText: There are several appliances that Rotom can inspirit, but the first one to be developed was the electric fan.

attack.text: Once during your first turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 Colorless Pokémon with 100 HP or less, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You can’t use more than 1 Fan Call Ability during your turn.

attack.name: Assault Landing
attack.text: If there is no Stadium in play, this attack does nothing.

name: Bouffalant

abilities.name: Curly Wall
abilities.text: As long as you have at least 1 other Bouffalant in play, all of your Basic {C} Pokémon take 60 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). The effect of Curly Wall doesn’t stack.

flavorText: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

attack.text: As long as you have at least 1 other Bouffalant in play, all of your Basic Colorless Pokémon take 60 less damage from attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). The effect of Curly Wall doesn’t stack.

attack.name: Boundless Power
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t attack.

name: Tornadus
flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

attack.name: Storm Barrier
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Fletchling
flavorText: Fletchling can be found in both rural and urban areas. They once had a huge territorial dispute with Squawkabilly. Fights broke out all over town.

attack.name: Send Back
attack.text: Switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: Its territory has a radius of just over a mile. If any bird Pokémon should enter, it will show them no mercy.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: When it gets excited, it vents sparks from the gaps between its feathers. These unburnable feathers are used as a fireproof material.

attack.name: Aero Chase
attack.text: If the Retreat Cost of your opponent’s Active Pokémon is ColorlessColorless or more, this attack does 110 more damage.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

attack.name: Knock Over
attack.text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

name: Dubwool

abilities.name: Soft Wool
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Weave a carpet from its springy wool, and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

attack.name: Knock Over
attack.text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

name: Lechonk
flavorText: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.

name: Cyclizar
flavorText: It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The rider’s body heat warms Cyclizar’s back and lifts the Pokémon’s spirit.

flavorText: While it is young, it uses the nutrients that are stored in the seed on its back in order to grow.

abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon that has 90 HP or less remaining to the Active Spot.

flavorText: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.

name: Lileep
flavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100,000,000 years ago.

attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

flavorText: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

name: Raboot
flavorText: While it prides itself on its varied kicking moves, it can also deliver powerful headbutts once its flames have heated up its forehead.

name: Squirtle
flavorText: When it feels threatened, it draws its limbs inside its shell and sprays water from its mouth.

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.

attack.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon.

name: Milcery
flavorText: When attacked, it tackles its foe and covers them in cream. With its foe either blinded or astonished by deliciousness, Milcery flees.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

attack.name: Calm Mind

name: Gulpin
flavorText: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
